parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Turbo Failure due to Clogged Oil Screen
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Turbo failure can cause a loss of power, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage, which can result in costly repairs and compromise vehicle safety.
Fuel line issues can cause gasoline leaks, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially cause nausea and discomfort to occupants due to the strong smell of gasoline.

The failure of the turbocharger can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of vehicle control, which can result in accidents, especially if it occurs at high speeds. The failure can also cause the engine to ignite due to metal-on-metal grinding of the turbo turbine, leading to a fire hazard.
symptoms: turbo wheel sheared off the shaft
no symptoms or warnings prior to failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The oil screen restriction can cause oil flow to the turbos to be restricted, leading to turbocharger failure, which can result in engine stalling and loss of vehicle control.
